British Reverend Charles Martin King Parsons was one of a handful of chaplains who helped liberate Bergen-Belsen in 1945 . 
  The camp was the final resting place for 50,000 Jews, Gypsies, homosexuals and the disabled . 
  Diarist Anne Frank and her sister Margot also died there . 
  Shortly after liberation by British and Canadian troops in 1945 it was torched to the ground . 
  Images were taken by Mr Parsons after the camp was liberated . 
 